    <item>
      <title>Re: Manastone taken out of PoK?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=243878#M243878</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;"Please stop with the personal disagreements on the boards.&amp;nbsp; If you have an issue with something someone has posted and wish to discuss it with them, take it to PMs."&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I read this a few times....and it sounded more silly each time I read it. I mean, were I to say here that "Halflings are too powerfull, and must be nerfed!!", then discussion to the contrary would need to by PM'd to me allowing my assertion to remain unchallenged on the board itself?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;More on-topic....&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Manastones are an EQ artifact. There are a finite number which exist, and with people retiring etc., that number only shrinks each year. What's more, they are tradeable, so it's possible that anyone might be fortunate enough to own one someday. If anything, they should be returned to a more useful status, and remain something to feel proud of.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;SoE has adopted a sort of double-standard when it comes to some of these items. HEBs for example were first removed from the game because they were too powerful.&amp;nbsp;SoE could have made them NODROP at that point, thus eliminating the pain of their next move, but they did not. In the days that followed the point when HEBs no longer dropped, their price skyrocked to numbers I'd never imagined. No item at the time was selling for as much....and then, one day...BAM! HEBs nerfed! Can you picure the look on the poor sucker's face who'd just payed 2 million platinum for the HEBs and their Eye which no longer agro'd mobs??&amp;nbsp;To add insult to injury, the HEBs are later included in the list of Super-Duper, removed-from-the-game items available from the Casino.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;SoE should show some class with the Manastone, and return it to its rightful place as an artifact. Give it a useful cast time (not like the goofy ManaRobe) if absolutely necessary for balance...or add an element of risk (on occasion it converts 2000 hps on a&amp;nbsp;click...or puts a "Lich-like" DoT on you making the hps--&amp;gt;mana conversion much heavier on the hps side).&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;-Morloc&lt;/P&gt;</description>
