&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;EM&gt;"No, for a truly level playing field, let's just give each and every caster his/her own manastone. And give non-clerics a CH spell that allows them to get back a huge chunk of health for a small fraction of the mana the stone gave them.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;If you're so darned positive that there's "nothing unbalancing about this stone at all," then there's no reason at all why the item shouldn't be allowed to drop like rain. I'll leave you the job of convincing devs."&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;There isn't such a thing as a&amp;nbsp;truly level playing field and in striving for one most game companies seem to just participate in endless rounds of nerfs.&amp;nbsp; Once uber item X or is removed or nerf, then slighly-less uber item Y becomes the new uber item, when that item or spell or ability is nerfed than slightly-less uber&amp;nbsp;item/spell/etc Z becomes the new uber.&amp;nbsp; MMORPG are&amp;nbsp;far too complex to balance properly - if you want true balance play Rock Paper Scissors.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Fortunately,&amp;nbsp; EQ is complex enough that the fact that item X or Y or Z is slightly unbalancing - doesn't seriously impact the greater world.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The point of a game shouldn't be too create a level playing field - but to reward players for playing well.&amp;nbsp; E.g. SOE could make manastones no trade so they can't be sold, and (if it brings them back into the game as a drop) make them more dificult to obtain rather than nerfing their use in PoK.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I'm all for finding creative ways for limiting items that are "uber"&amp;nbsp; (as SoE did with Manastones by prohibiting their use in new zones) but not for taking them out of the game or nerfing them to uselessness.&amp;nbsp; Doing so is a slap at the players who gamed hard to obtain them (note I've never owned a manastone and have no plans to ever by one).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I guess I like the idea of having items to aspire too - that are more than just better stats.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
